cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper deals with binding-time analysis for logic programs, which is a topic closely related to programming languages.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper formalizes the unfolding aspect of an on-line partial deduction system as a Prolog program, which is a logic programming language. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses turning an on-line system into an off-line system, which is a software engineering concern.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses abstract interpretation to collect information about the run-time behavior of the program, which is a technique commonly used in AI for program analysis.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory): The paper deals with formalizing the behavior of a partial deduction system, which is a topic related to formal languages and automata theory.
